    scoring='r2')

import numpy as np
y_pred = [1.5, 1.9, 2.3, 1.4]
y_true = [1.6, 2.2, 2.2, 1.5]

sum_diffs = 0
for prediction, truth in zip(y_pred, y_true):
    sum_diffs += (prediction - truth) ** 2  # np.abs(prediction - truth)
mean_diff = sum_diffs / len(y_pred)
print(np.sqrt(mean_diff))
